      "highlights" : "Wind slabs represent the main danger.",
      "comment" : "A lot of snow fell in the last two days over a wide area. As a consequence of new snow and a strong wind from southerly directions, wind slabs formed in particular at intermediate and high altitudes. <br/> The fresh wind slabs can be released easily or naturally. In particular in gullies and bowls, and behind abrupt changes in the terrain and on wind-loaded slopes large avalanches are possible. <br/> <br/> Snow sport activities outside marked and open pistes call for experience and great restraint."
